<h3>Greptile Summary</h3>

This PR reclassifies silent (no stderr) non-zero exits from the `acpx` backend as `ACP_BACKEND_UNAVAILABLE` rather than the generic `ACP_TURN_FAILED`, giving users more actionable guidance (`/acp doctor`) when the backend process disappears without a structured error. Permission-denied exits (code 5) are deliberately kept as `ACP_TURN_FAILED` to preserve the existing configuration guidance.

The change is applied in two layers:

- **`extensions/acpx/src/runtime.ts`** – `resolveSilentAcpxExitErrorCode` is called directly when the ACP runtime detects a silent exit in `runTurn` (streaming path) and in the private `runControlCommand` helper (control-command path).
- **`src/acp/control-plane/manager.core.ts`** – A defensive regex-based fallback (`resolveTurnFailureFallbackCode`) catches the rare case where the runtime emits a plain `Error` (not `AcpRuntimeError`) with the `"acpx exited with code N"` message text.

